The dmd D compiler has a built in coverage analyzer, while not quite what you describe, comes close:<p><pre><code>       |bool foo(bool i, bool j) {
      2|    return i ||
      1|           j;
       |}
       |
       |void main() {
      1|    foo(true, false);
      1|    foo(false, false);
       |}
</code></pre>
It&#x27;ll give an execution count on each statement, and logical expression operands count as separate statements. I&#x27;ve found that when this is used in conjunction with a test suite to ensure that the tests cause every code path to be executed, the code becomes remarkably free of bugs.
